74 Existing law requires the superintendent of schools in a school district in this State which
75 has more than 100,000 pupils enrolled in its public schools (currently the Clark County
76 School District) to assign a school associate superintendent to oversee one or more local
77 school precincts. (NRS 388G.620) Existing law prescribes the duties of a school associate
78 superintendent, including requiring a school associate superintendent to provide a report in
79 person, not less than quarterly, to the governing body of each city and county within which a
80 local school precinct to which he or she is assigned to oversee is located. (NRS 388G.630)
81 Section 7 of this bill eliminates the requirement to report to a county.
82 Exiting law authorizes a board of county commissioners to grant a franchise to construct,
83 install, operate, and maintain street railways, electric light, heat and power lines, gas and
84 water mains and telephone lines, among certain other things. (NRS 709.050) Any person or
85 entity desiring a franchise is required to file an application in writing with the board of county
86 commissioners wherein the franchise is to be exercised. (NRS 709.060) Notice of such an
87 application is required to be given at the next regular meeting of the board and is required to
88 be: (1) published once each week for 4 consecutive weeks in a newspaper of general
89 circulation published in the county, subject to certain exceptions; and (2) posted in three
90 public places nearest where the application will take effect, and if more than one
91 unincorporated town is affected, posted in three public places in each of the unincorporated
92 towns. (NRS 709.070) Section 8 of this bill revises such requirements to post the notice from
93 three places to one place if more than one unincorporated town is affected by reducing the
94 postings required in public places in each of the unincorporated towns.
